sonated so powerfully around the world. Investigating the roles of producers, consumers, and distributors, Marla Frederick takes a unique look at the ministries, the communities they enter, and the global markets of competition that buffer them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAfrican American evangelistszUnited States. 0aAfrican American evangelists. 0aTelevision broadcasting, American. 0aTelevision in religionzUnited States. 0aWomen evangelistszUnited States. 4aAfrican American religion. 4aChristianity. 4aMedia. 4aReligion. 4aTelevangelism. 4agender. 4aglobalization. 4aprosperity gospel. 4arace. 4asexuality. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311070398640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080479700940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804797009423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804797009.jpg  a978-3-11-070398-6  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles